  "texts": [
    "Lai [22] proposed to exploit the relationship between training tasks for FSED,which computes prototypes based on cross-task modeling and presents a regularization to enforce prediction consistency of classifiers across tasks.",
    "Shen et al. [32] proposed AKE-BML, which leverages the external knowledge base FrameNet to learn prototype representations for event types and alleviates the insufficient sample diversity problem in few-shot learning.",
    "Besides, AKE-BML presented a novel knowledge adaptation mechanism to tackle the uncertainty and incompleteness issues in knowledge coverage.",
    "Chen [1] found that the trigger is a confounder of the context and the result, which makes previous FSED methods much easier to overfit triggers.",
    "To resolve this problem, they propose to intervene on the context via backdoor adjustment during training."
  ],
